Hungary Ex-Premier Bajnai Breaks Nose in Soccer Game, Blikk Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-08-17T07:24:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/hungary-ex-premier-bajnai-breaks-nose-in-soccer-game-blikk-says.html
Gordon Bajnai,  Hungary ’s former
prime minister who is a goalie on an amateur soccer team, broke
his nose and had to be taken off the field by an ambulance after
he was kicked in the face by a striker, Blikk reported, citing
Bajnai’s teammates.  Bajnai received stitches and was released from the
hospital, the tabloid daily said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
